Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.56,0:00:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.88,0:00:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.56,0:00:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.76,0:00:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.84,0:00:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, every year we like to take\Nthree of the latest super-expensive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.64,0:00:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,supercars over to continental Europe\Nto find out which one is best.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.28,0:00:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But these days, thanks to\Nthe financial crisis over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.57,0:00:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that's proving to be a bit tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.89,0:01:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in Britain, the economy\Nis not that great
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.89,0:01:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but from what we understand,\Nover the border in Spain,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.25,0:01:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,things are absolutely dreadful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.10,0:01:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, so it really wouldn't be\Nappropriate for us to do what
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.26,0:01:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we usually do and turn up in three\Nmillion-pound V12 monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.86,0:01:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because that would just look\Nlike we were showing off. Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.70,0:01:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but because it's Spain, and\Ntherefore likely to be very sunny,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.30,0:01:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we did want to be able to\Ntake the roof off, so what
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.70,0:01:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we've done is we've organised three\Nbudget convertibles for a nice drive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.98,0:01:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,from here in Britain to Madrid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.86,0:01:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gone for the second cheapest\Ncar in the Ferrari range,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.74,0:01:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not necessarily a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.30,0:02:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like choosing\Nwine in a restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.10,0:02:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As we all know, the second cheapest\Nis always your best bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.06,0:02:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the 458 and this is the new\NSpider version, available
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.54,0:02:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,now for a very reasonable £198,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.46,0:02:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gone for the new McLaren\Nconvertible,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.50,0:02:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12C Spider, which amazingly\Nis even cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.94,0:02:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just £195,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.34,0:02:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,For that sort of money,\NI was expecting a sort of Scout hut
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.62,0:02:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,with windscreen wipers,\Nbut I've got sat nav,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.02,0:02:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got air conditioning,\Ncentral locking, electric windows,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.26,0:02:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,power steering,\Nit's really not bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it comes to value,\NIron Man had trumped both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.62,0:02:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, hello, viewers,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you would expect,\NI have done it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.46,0:03:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I've chosen the Audi R8\Nconvertible, the V10 version,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.14,0:03:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,a mere sniff as £121,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.22,0:03:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Although, to be honest,\Nfrom where I'm sitting,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.66,0:03:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I really can't work out why it's\Nso much cheaper than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it has the biggest engine,\N5.2 litre V10 from a Lamborghini...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.90,0:03:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It has four-wheel drive, it has\Nthe best standard equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.74,0:03:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the perfect car\Nfor a cash-strapped economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.46,0:03:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Our first port of call, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.38,0:03:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't look very cash-strapped\Nat all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it was Puerto Banus,\Nstill thriving because
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.82,0:03:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,every summer, people from Essex come\Nhere to make themselves more orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.66,0:03:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Their taste may be quiet\Nand restrained but it's keeping
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.10,0:04:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the local economy going and it also\Ngave James an idea for a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.94,0:04:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the whole point of a budget\Nsupercar is that it should be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.50,0:04:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,understated, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.82,0:04:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.30,0:04:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to drive from here to\Nthe other end of the harbour,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.42,0:04:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,one at a time, and the winner is the\None whose car is least photographed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.18,0:04:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,James, I'm in a yellow metal\Nflake convertible McLaren. I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.50,0:04:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's going to get photographed\Nall the time. Well, you chose it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.10,0:04:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After dusk, and with a camera fitted\Nto record flashes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.54,0:04:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,James set off, confident his\Ngrey Audi would be like a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.66,0:04:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.94,0:04:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"People of Puerto Banus..."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.82,0:04:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"James May driving through\Nyour town."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.62,0:04:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"Now! Get your pictures."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.74,0:04:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Tweet sent. Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.10,0:04:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Annoyingly, though, our plan didn't\Nwork very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.78,0:05:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,See, it doesn't draw attention,\Nthe car doesn't draw attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.54,0:05:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No flashes whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.26,0:05:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go, a successful, largely\Nphotograph-free run.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.82,0:05:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,'The Ferrari attracted quite a lot\Nmore attention.'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.82,0:05:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.54,0:05:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I got hit there,\Nthat was a lucky shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.34,0:05:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,'..even after I'd finished.'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.50,0:05:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That does not count! Can I have\Na picture of your car, mate?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.74,0:05:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Jeremy set off in his metal\Nflake yellow McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is astonishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.22,0:05:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A McLaren Formula One car would get\Nless attention than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.06,0:05:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'Once I'd reached\Nthe finish line...'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No photographs! No photographs here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.30,0:05:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,'..the producers handed\Nover the score.'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.38,0:06:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really tired. Read them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.90,0:06:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I read them out?\NJust read them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just...\NI just want to go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, no need to do\Nit in reverse order, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.50,0:06:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it in the order we went.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Audi, 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.78,0:06:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,22 people took your picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.42,0:06:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that good or bad? Ferrari...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,47 people took your picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.02,0:06:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How many flashes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.38,0:06:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you lost. Bloody hell.\NYou did lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.14,0:06:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,438!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.58,0:06:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as a budget supercar,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,McLaren has not done well in terms\Nof understatement, has it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.98,0:06:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's a bit conspicuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day,\Nwe left the affluent coast
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.34,0:06:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and headed north into what people\Ncall the real Spain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.78,0:06:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Spain, six million unemployed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.26,0:07:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have a smaller population\Nthan we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.42,0:07:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,two million households have no\Nincome at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.58,0:07:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,57% youth unemployment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.18,0:07:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,'Right now, though, James was\Ndealing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.02,0:07:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,'with rather more serious issues.'
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.54,0:07:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The cabin is too blustery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got both the windows up\Nand I have the windshield thing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.90,0:07:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,at the back up, but my hair\Nstill whips me in the eyeballs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.78,0:07:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I know some of you are going, "Why\Ndon't you get your hair cut, then?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.70,0:07:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people have lots of hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,James has now cured the appalling\Nbuffeting in the Audi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.18,0:07:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with the simple addition\Nof a bandanna...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.34,0:07:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,..which makes him look very manly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.94,0:07:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,'We decided to stop in the next\Ntown for some coffee, and here
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.62,0:07:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,'we saw just how badly hit Spain\Nhas been by the financial crisis.'
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.82,0:08:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all brand-new flats.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.78,0:08:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.46,0:08:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, nobody at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.74,0:08:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got all of the infrastructure.\NStreet lights,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.42,0:08:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,pedestrian crossings,\Nbut no people at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.54,0:08:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a scene from a horror film.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Nyou hear about these ghost towns
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.74,0:08:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but you don't really think\Nthey exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,'Still, on the up-side,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,'the echoey empty streets did\Nprovide the perfect setting
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.70,0:08:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,'for a noise test.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.78,0:08:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,'I parked at the far end of town
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.98,0:08:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,'while Jeremy fired up his\Ndecibel-o-meter.'
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When I say Jeremy has\Na decibel-o-meter,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.58,0:08:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the decibel-o-meter app.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.26,0:09:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Slightly worried about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.66,0:09:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's got two more cylinders\Nthan we have. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.58,0:09:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got ten. So that's two more...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.42,0:09:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And one more cylinder firing per...\NBank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.58,0:09:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. So that's two more...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.42,0:09:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got two banks of five,\Nwe've got two banks of four.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.06,0:09:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, so he's got two more\Nexplosions per...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.54,0:09:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Per... Every time there's\Nfiring, there'll be one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.78,0:09:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but that's on each bank. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Top Gear,\Nthe world's leading motoring show.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.38,0:09:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.22,0:09:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,105. 105. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.26,0:09:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'Next it was the McLaren's turn.'
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.58,0:09:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm ready. Oh, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.54,0:09:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.22,0:09:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, start quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:10:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it in second so\Nwhen we get near the decibel-o-meter
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.54,0:10:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at the top of the rev range.\NHere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.78,0:10:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Now, that was mighty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's my score? 105.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.90,0:10:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What? 105 again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.18,0:10:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What, the same as his? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.90,0:10:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very much the same, yes.\NRubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.74,0:10:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,'With Jeremy still complaining,\NI lined up the Ferrari.'
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.94,0:10:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet he just floors it\Nfrom the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.38,0:10:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he has. Daft as a brush.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got to go as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.94,0:10:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupidest man in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.30,0:10:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,107. Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.70,0:10:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond was, as ever,\Ngracious in victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.38,0:10:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha! Come on, it's still more,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.34,0:10:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and those last few decibels\Nare harder to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.38,0:11:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the last few miles an hour\Nbecause of aerodynamics.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.02,0:11:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, wait, that must mean you lose.\NIt does. No, you got 105...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.90,0:11:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's budget supercars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.22,0:11:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Discretion. The quietist. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.10,0:11:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? We've just decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.38,0:11:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the rules have just changed\Nat the exact moment at which you lost
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.78,0:11:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and I won.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.18,0:11:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We never discussed rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.94,0:11:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,'Back on the move, we headed for the\NSierra Nevada mountains on what is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,'not only the highest road in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.86,0:11:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,'but also one of the most\Nspectacular.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.14,0:11:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,'This is perfect supercar country.'
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.58,0:11:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When the McLaren MP4 first came out\N18 months ago, it was better than
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.26,0:11:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a Ferrari 458 in every measurable\Nway, but it lacked panache,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it lacked zing, it lacked\Nexcitement,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.06,0:12:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it felt clinical and antiseptic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.18,0:12:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,'Since then, though,\Nthey've made lots of little changes,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.50,0:12:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,'so now there's more noise\Nand even more power.'
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.46,0:12:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But the big thing is - all that sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what the McLaren was always\Nmeant to be - open top.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.46,0:12:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,'By taking off the roof, they've\Nturned the McLaren from a car
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.86,0:12:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'you admire into a car you want.'
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.58,0:12:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you really, really want this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.90,0:13:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no denying it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.42,0:13:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ferrari is down on power\Ncompared to the McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.78,0:13:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Overall, it makes about 50 brake\Nhorsepower but it is lighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.82,0:13:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the lightest here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.66,0:13:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, I am not complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.58,0:13:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The point and squirt-ability of this\Nthing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.34,0:13:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, a bit of wrestling to get it\Naround the corner and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.82,0:13:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ya! What a soundtrack!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.90,0:13:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,'Meanwhile,\Nback in the cheap seats...'
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, serious stuff. This Audi is,\Ngive or take a few quid,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.70,0:13:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,£70,000 cheaper than the other two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.70,0:13:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.54,0:13:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's got a slightly\Nlower top speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.14,0:13:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's slightly\Nslower at 60 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.30,0:13:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It weighs quite a bit more,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.50,0:14:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the best will in the world,\Nit does have a second-hand engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does have four-wheel-drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.78,0:14:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,'And then there's the new gearbox.'
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.94,0:14:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to be the single clutch\Nflappy paddle type.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.14,0:14:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's now twin clutch, seven\Nspeed,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.14,0:14:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is absolutely\Nfantastic. Listen to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.78,0:14:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A gear, a gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.50,0:14:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously, it is superb.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.66,0:14:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,'Intoxicated by our cut-price\Nsupercars, we climbed higher
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.86,0:14:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,'and higher.'
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.62,0:14:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Hammond,\Ntry and live with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.14,0:14:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,God, it announces its arrival!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.34,0:14:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the road got better and better.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.98,0:14:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.58,0:14:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.26,0:15:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This road is just staggering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.90,0:15:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How much did it cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.74,0:15:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.70,0:15:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What, that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.10,0:15:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And stop.\NWhat? Hang on a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.62,0:15:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the road was really\Nquiet? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.70,0:15:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to know why? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.74,0:15:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't go anywhere.\NThat's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.86,0:15:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see the road that\Nleads to a city.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.14,0:15:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be absolutely awesome.\NIt must be if it goes somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How much money did that cost?\NYes, a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.98,0:15:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what we learned on the road\Nto absolutely nowhere at all
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.86,0:15:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is just how fast that McLaren is.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.42,0:15:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was fast\Nwhen it came out, but now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.14,0:16:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's astonishing and when you're in\Na Ferrari you do not expect to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.22,0:16:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,be left behind by anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.54,0:16:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,On the straights,\Nit just walks away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.46,0:16:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like you were in a Nissan\NMicra and I was in a supercar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.66,0:16:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the straights,\Nthe corners were worse
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because following the McLaren,\Nyou watch it go round at a speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.66,0:16:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and you think "I'll go around at\Nthe same speed" and you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.62,0:16:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.02,0:16:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I just say, the McLaren is epic,\NI agree with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.38,0:16:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the two tests we conducted\Nso far, the victor is the Audi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.34,0:16:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it tied with\Nthe McLaren for one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.30,0:16:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We also did an economy run. And the\NAudi won that, as well. Yes, it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, later on, there will be\Nmore cut-price supercar larks
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.26,0:16:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from Spain. In the meantime,\Nhere is the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.90,0:16:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I've got an announcement to\Nmake first. Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.70,0:16:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, last week, in a bid to show\Nthat Britain is not too crowded to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.22,0:17:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,have fun in a nice car, I took\Na Ferrari to this road, and I said
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.86,0:17:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that even though this was\Njust 40 miles from London
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.42,0:17:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in Hertfordshire...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,..there was no traffic at all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.70,0:17:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you could still enjoy it\Nin the Ferrari that I was using.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.14,0:17:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have been inundated with\Ncomplaints, and I do mean inundated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.06,0:17:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been a lot. A lot.\NPeople were absolutely furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"How dare the BBC say this is\NHertfordshire?! It plainly isn't."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.90,0:17:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're right,\NI admit it, and I apologise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.86,0:17:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not Hertfordshire.\NIt's Buckinghamshire, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.82,0:17:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, well spotted,\Nall of you, for seeing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.18,0:17:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You were on the ball, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, now, we've got some important\Nconsumer news for everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.14,0:17:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When you go to a car showroom now,\Nthe salesman will try to sell you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.14,0:17:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,lots of electronic bits\Nand bobs for your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.02,0:17:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's our Top Gear top tip -\Ndon't bother with any of them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.62,0:17:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't work,\Nany of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.62,0:17:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Bluetooth. Bluetooth never works.\NIt doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.46,0:17:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond uses it and it's like he's\Nsitting at the bottom of a river.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.14,0:18:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to be fair, sometimes I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.58,0:18:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I tell you the thing that\Ndoesn't work the most of all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Voice activation.\NThat's just a shouting match.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.54,0:18:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You're driving along, don't have to\Ntake your hands off the wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.34,0:18:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You go, "Call Richard Hammond."\N"Collapsing suspension".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.02,0:18:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It does!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.46,0:18:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's misunderstood me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.74,0:18:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Call Richard Hammond."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.82,0:18:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"Deflating tyres."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.54,0:18:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.78,0:18:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"Reinflate tyres!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.82,0:18:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Reinflate tyres!"\N"Calling Richard Hammond."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.98,0:18:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is that, in the olden\Ndays, when it first came out,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.86,0:18:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,voice activation was just for the\Nradio or the satellite navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.86,0:18:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's for every single\Nfeature on the car
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and in your life, and it has to\Nunderstand every accent
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.10,0:18:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.62,0:18:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Och aye the noo."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.34,0:18:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"All right, pet?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.34,0:18:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It just can't cope. So, you're\Ndriving along, you go, "Radio Two."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.90,0:18:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"Accessing bank account."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.62,0:18:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.14,0:18:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Transferring funds."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.86,0:18:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God, no, don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,While we're having a moan,\NI don't like electric boot closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.10,0:19:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,With you on that. What was\Nthe matter with slamming the boot?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.18,0:19:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of doing that,\Nit's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.10,0:19:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea is that you press the button
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.62,0:19:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and the boot sets off and you can\Nget in your car, but it's so slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.34,0:19:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time you've got in your car,\Nyour dog had seen its opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.58,0:19:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and made a break for freedom,\Nhe's in the traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.26,0:19:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Or worse, it detects your\Nshopping in the boot
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.06,0:19:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and it thinks,\N"That could be a child."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look, it's a packet of dog\Nbiscuits, it's not a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.90,0:19:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Firing airbag in three..."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.50,0:19:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't fire the airbag!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.10,0:19:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Modern cars are deeply irritating\Nbecause of the electronics.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.34,0:19:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I move it on now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.42,0:19:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, last week\NI asked if you would send in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.90,0:19:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,photographs of Jeremy\Non his new bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.62,0:19:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because... Well, I didn't expect to\Nget anything because, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.18,0:19:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't believe he'd bought\Na bike. I have! Well... I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.74,0:19:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know, I now believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you have, because somebody\NHAS sent in a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.78,0:20:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And here he is -\NJeremy on his bicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.70,0:20:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, er... It's working.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.46,0:20:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You are losing weight.\NYou're trimming down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.06,0:20:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not my bike.\NI haven't got stabilisers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.30,0:20:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, it's pretty accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got some serious news.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.34,0:20:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of cars these days have got\Na sport button on them, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.62,0:20:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea is you push it\Nand it makes everything more taut\Nand more racy, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.26,0:20:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've long harboured\Na suspicion that it doesn't\Nactually make the car go any faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.06,0:20:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So last week we did a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.14,0:20:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got a new Golf GTI\Ndown here, which incidentally,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.18,0:20:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is a brilliant, brilliant car.\NExtremely good. It's properly good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.22,0:20:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we got The Stig,\Nput him in normal mode,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.78,0:20:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,sent him around the track\Nand he did a 129.6, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.78,0:20:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We then put it in sport\Nwhich beefed up the suspension
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.54,0:20:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the front differential\Nand it made the steering heavier
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.42,0:21:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and it quickened the throttle, OK?\NIn sport, 129.6.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.54,0:21:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What, exactly the same?\NExactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.02,0:21:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We then put it in comfort mode,\Nmakes everything soft and gooey.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.42,0:21:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,129.5. Fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.86,0:21:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.98,0:21:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That is confirmation\Nthat the sport button just makes\Na car more uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.22,0:21:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it shouldn't say "sport",
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.70,0:21:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it should just say, "worse".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.42,0:21:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there's a new supercar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.10,0:21:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It is called the... Icona Vulcano.\NHere it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.66,0:21:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, did you do\Nthat publicity photograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.94,0:21:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what\NI call a publicity shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.66,0:21:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I love that very much.\NNot sure about the car, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.94,0:21:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They say it has a V12 hybrid,\Nbut they won't tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.10,0:21:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where the V12's from or\Nhow the hybrid system works.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.26,0:21:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All they will say\Nis it develops 950 horsepower
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.90,0:21:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and will go 217 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.06,0:21:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it? Mmm, mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.38,0:21:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I brought this car up\Nis their chief design director,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.70,0:21:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,his name is Samuel Chuffart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.46,0:22:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Give over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.10,0:22:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.86,0:22:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is not Chuffart.\NIt's not! Chuffart. Lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.06,0:22:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a man with fond\Nmemories of his school days!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.54,0:22:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Every register, "Oh, no, it's got to\NChristian, I'm next." "Chuffart".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.42,0:22:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"A-ha-ha-ha." I bet the\Nnovelty never wore off for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.34,0:22:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently,\Nhe worked at Jaguar for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.86,0:22:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure what happened there.\NThey probably had to let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.70,0:22:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So now he's ended up in Italy,\Nbecause that is an Italian firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.26,0:22:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They're actually making\Nthe car in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine what\Nthe wiring's going to be like?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.06,0:22:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Chuffart in Italian probably means\N"hat penis" anyway, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.06,0:22:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We actually asked our researchers\Nto call up this company and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.06,0:22:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Can you tell us more about\Nthe car?" And not one of them
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.34,0:22:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,could get through the beginning bit\Nof the call without bursting...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.22,0:22:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The receptionist on the other end\Nmust be used to the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.70,0:22:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ringing and there's\Nsomeone laughing,\N"Yeah, I'll put you through."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.78,0:22:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Hello, Chuffart."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:22:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably just answers the phone\Nwith the words, "Yes, that is\Nmy name. Let's clear the air now."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.06,0:23:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how that picture came about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.34,0:23:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone lit a match just after\NChuff farted!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.82,0:23:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving on. Because this week we are\Ntesting the McLaren 12C Spider,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.82,0:23:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ferrari 458 Spider\Nand the Audi R8 V10.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.98,0:23:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me guess, is it Spider?\NDo you know, it is. It is a Spider.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.98,0:23:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We have chosen budget supercars\Nbecause we are in Spain,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where the economic problems\Nare terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.86,0:23:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\Nso far we've been to a ghost town.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.06,0:23:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It had a hospital,\Nit had a school, had restaurants,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.34,0:23:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,had thousands of houses and flats,\Nbut no people at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.42,0:23:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been on a road that\Nwent nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.34,0:23:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like filming in\Na ghost country, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.42,0:23:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we pick up the story\Nafter a night in a hotel in Granada.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.54,0:24:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We headed north\Nthe following morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.46,0:24:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,worried that we'd hit the rush-hour\Ntraffic. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.38,0:24:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's only three cars on this\Nmotorway and we're in all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.78,0:24:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that.\NOur own personal motorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.98,0:24:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always wanted a motorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.14,0:24:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Since no-one was around,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.62,0:24:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we thought we would see\Nhow fast our cars would go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.94,0:24:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need to find a straight bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.86,0:24:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is quite straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.82,0:24:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200 miles an hour, this slight\Ncorner becomes a hairpin bend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.34,0:24:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We need arrow straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.50,0:24:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,'When we did eventually find a long\Nenough straight, it had goats on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.42,0:24:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,'So we were about to give up\Non our top speed run, but then...'
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.34,0:25:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, an airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.98,0:25:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Chaps, is that an airport? I just\Nthought... Yes, aeropuerto, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.54,0:25:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if the runway's as busy\Nas the roads,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.90,0:25:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we might be able to\Nuse the runway for our speed test.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.18,0:25:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,God, there's some parking available!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.42,0:25:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.78,0:25:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Er... Where is everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.06,0:25:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,'We went inside to\Nlook for someone in charge.'
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.50,0:25:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.22,0:25:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.26,0:25:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,'But the whole place\Nwas completely deserted.'
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.42,0:25:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The computers are all on, look!\NI can make a baggage check.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.06,0:25:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can log on!\NI've got one of those things that\Ngoes... I can check you in!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.70,0:26:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha-ha-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.70,0:26:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The wheel's coming off.\NMy wheel's come off!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.98,0:26:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. I'll be Lufthansa.\NI am sorry, the gate is closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.70,0:26:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, can you just open it? Nein.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.14,0:26:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't got a passport,\NI've just got a selection of weapons\Nand some concealed drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.06,0:26:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, though,\Nwe found what we came for.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.98,0:26:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a runway over there,\NI believe. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.90,0:26:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,'But since there was no-one around\Nto ask for permission to use it,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.66,0:26:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,'we had to improvise.'
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.98,0:26:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be possible for us\Nto drive on the runway here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.26,0:26:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any flight traffic today?\NNo, it's very quiet today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.34,0:26:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.50,0:26:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,With permission granted,\Nwe headed out to the runway.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.14,0:26:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, I've got it.\NI've got it. It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.22,0:27:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do manual labour,\Nyou know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.70,0:27:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.66,0:27:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.86,0:27:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The runway was\Na whopping 2.5 miles long.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.06,0:27:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,More than enough to max our cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.10,0:27:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond elected to go first.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.42,0:27:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always nervous\Nwhen he drives in a straight line.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.42,0:27:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Richard Hammond, can you drive\Nin a straight line down a runway?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.26,0:27:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"Yes, what can possibly go\Nwrong with that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.34,0:27:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit the launch control button\Nwith it, in race and manual.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.98,0:27:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it max revs, my right foot.\NENGINE REVS
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.06,0:27:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Left foot off.\NRight, we're away!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.14,0:27:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It does the first gear\Nchange for me, now it's up to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.82,0:27:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and already we're doing 85, 90...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.94,0:27:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,100 miles an hour, that quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.22,0:28:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn, this thing is fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.98,0:28:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at the dust cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.42,0:28:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,138, 141.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.62,0:28:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear the grit\Nhitting the underside of the car.\NThere's a lot of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.18,0:28:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Seventh gear has just been hit.\N175 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.70,0:28:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Still accelerating hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.78,0:28:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the line, 186...87, 88.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.42,0:28:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Ferrari, accelerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.22,0:28:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that is a Ferrari at full chat.\N90. 91.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.50,0:28:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,92.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.54,0:28:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,92, 93.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.34,0:28:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,193 miles an hour.\NTop speed achieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.42,0:28:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Next up, it was James,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.10,0:28:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who decided to use absolutely\Nall of the available space.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.58,0:28:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, here we go. Sport,\Nsport suspension, air con is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.06,0:28:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Manual one. Here we go at the max.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.86,0:29:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, here he comes now.\NCaptain Slow is his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.86,0:29:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the Italians call him\N"Mr Slowly".
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.74,0:29:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 80.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.74,0:29:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know at some point in that car,\Nwhen he's doing his run,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.34,0:29:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he is saying, "buffeting".
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.14,0:29:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Buffeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.62,0:29:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He's moving along\Nin the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.06,0:29:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's weird to think James May\Nin that, doing that speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.94,0:29:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A spaniel in control of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.34,0:29:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Indicated 175, 177. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.06,0:29:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That said 186.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.14,0:29:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that modern-day\Nspeedos are frighteningly accurate,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.34,0:29:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew what speed I had to beat -\NHammond's, 193.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.46,0:29:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, launch control. First gear.\NPress launch. Launch active.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.58,0:29:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Three, two, one. Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.90,0:29:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow, that's quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.54,0:30:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,80 miles an hour already.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.10,0:30:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here he comes.\NHe's moving at tremendous speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.18,0:30:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,140. I'm taking manual control now
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.18,0:30:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to lock in in six.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.46,0:30:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to go into seventh
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.26,0:30:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because that will slow it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.42,0:30:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! 191, 193.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.22,0:30:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,194, 195, 196, 197.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.62,0:30:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,197 again.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.14,0:30:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm through\Nand I've indicated...198.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.94,0:30:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Victory, therefore, is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.38,0:30:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,'Annoyingly,\Nthough, we weren't finished,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.70,0:30:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,'because James had come up\Nwith an idea.'
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.18,0:30:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a drag race,\Nbut because of the weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.70,0:30:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,especially what it's doing today,\Nyou have to start
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.54,0:30:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with your roof down and you have to\Nfinish with your roof up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.98,0:31:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not quite as simple\Nas it sounds. Well, no, it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.06,0:31:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I can operate this roof\Nwhile I'm driving. So can I.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.14,0:31:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't. You can't. No, Ferrari,\Nyou have to... You have to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.30,0:31:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means... Hang on! No,\Nactually this is quite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.38,0:31:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do 19 miles an hour\Nand put the roof up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.70,0:31:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How fast can you go? 31.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.10,0:31:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're joking?\NBut officially, your roof, I think,\Ngoes up in 14 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.74,0:31:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine is about 19.\NThis is very complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.98,0:31:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the flag drops. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.62,0:31:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I set off,\Nbut I can only go 19 miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.26,0:31:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,while the roof is coming up.\NThen I can go. Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.66,0:31:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go to 31 miles an hour...\NBut I have to stay there for longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.86,0:31:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your roof takes\Nlonger to go up. You can't set off\Nat all until your roof is up.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.38,0:31:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But then... Go like hell.\NYeah, you launch control\Nand go like hell. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.02,0:31:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Having settled on a half-mile\Ndistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.30,0:31:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we lined up, and our Spanish starter\Nbegan the countdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.18,0:31:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Tres, dos, uno...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.50,0:32:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin, we begin, we begin.\NI daren't put it in launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.82,0:32:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They're moving away,\NI'm not going anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.86,0:32:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Less than 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.98,0:32:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,18 miles an hour. 19. 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.86,0:32:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.38,0:32:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I have exceeded\Nthe roof speed. Argh!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.86,0:32:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Bang!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.46,0:32:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God. Struggling for grip.\NWindows are going up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.02,0:32:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Roof latched! I am away!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.46,0:32:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I've passed James. Ha-ha!\NHa-ha! Oh BLEEP!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.10,0:32:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I did that wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.22,0:32:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We lined up for a second attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.94,0:32:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, glasses on so I can read\Nwhen the roof is latched.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.78,0:32:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, keep your finger on the\Nbutton and concentrate on the speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.62,0:33:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go. Keep it below 19 miles\Nan hour, Jeremy. 18, 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.14,0:33:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I wait until the roof is up and just\Nbefore the back hatch goes down,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.18,0:33:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hit the launch control\Nbutton. There.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.98,0:33:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.50,0:33:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This feels astonishingly slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.02,0:33:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,19, oh, 20.\NRoof operation in progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.78,0:33:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's down. I can go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.94,0:33:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Roof closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.02,0:33:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm changing gear with my left hand.\NHow multi-tasking was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.74,0:33:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I am passing James May.\NThey're getting closer to the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.50,0:33:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Jeremy is going to cross now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.06,0:33:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm getting closer to the Audi\Nby the second. Hammond's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.58,0:33:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get him,\NI'm going to get him!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.26,0:33:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Second. Oh-ho-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.98,0:33:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Victory has been mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.78,0:34:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Weirdly, though,\NJames had a different view.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.02,0:34:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The Audi's basically won\Nall of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.66,0:34:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry James, I think\Nyou'll find the McLaren\Ngot there miles before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.78,0:34:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Highest top speed, McLaren.\NSo the McLaren has won both things.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.50,0:34:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,However, could I draw your attention\Nto a few things?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.78,0:34:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A completely ruined back wheel,\Nsame on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.70,0:34:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to remind you of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.14,0:34:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Up here we find a very badly chipped\Nwindscreen. Hammond did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.14,0:34:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter who did it,\Nit's very badly chipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.50,0:34:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,YOU also have a very badly chipped\Nwindscreen. Where is it? Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.90,0:34:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You have ruined wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.54,0:34:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look down here, our cameraman\Nwants to come and see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.26,0:34:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This bit of the bodywork\Nhas actually been eaten away.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.78,0:34:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,'And that wasn't the only problem\Ncaused by the dust
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.78,0:34:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,'and grit on the unused runway.'
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.78,0:34:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look underneath!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.62,0:34:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.70,0:34:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Audi, meanwhile,\Nwas totally unmarked.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.74,0:35:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do the Germans put paint on\Nin such a way that it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.82,0:35:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,then come off?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.02,0:35:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they are Germans and it is\Nimpossible to paint a car badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.62,0:35:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Conceding James' point,\Nwe got back on the road
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.70,0:35:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and with evening approaching, it was\Ntime to look for somewhere to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.94,0:35:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Chaps? Yes. I've had yet another\Nbrilliant idea. Have you? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.26,0:35:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Ninstead of looking for a hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.38,0:35:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't we just go into the next\Ntown and help ourselves to a house?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.78,0:35:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.26,0:35:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.42,0:35:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the next town,\Nwe started househunting,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.78,0:35:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly we were spoilt for\Nchoice. I would quite like a view.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.14,0:35:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that one's garden's all\Novergrown. I don't fancy that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.54,0:35:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want one with a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.86,0:36:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How about 53? Do you like 53? Or 55?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.98,0:36:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As a number, I prefer 55.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.74,0:36:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,'With that settled, we moved in.'\NOh, it's nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.42,0:36:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. Junk mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.26,0:36:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a bedroom?\NI'm going to have this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.42,0:36:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hasn't actually got a bed in it,\Nbut that'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.46,0:36:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, look at this! I've got a bath,\Nbidet, bog. Hammond?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.58,0:36:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? We've found your room. Let\Nme guess, is it small? It's low.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.82,0:36:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not. Oh, it's an en suite.\NLook at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.66,0:36:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.58,0:36:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,'Having brightened the place up\Nwith some decorations,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.42,0:36:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'Jeremy cooked us a paella\Nwhile we discussed our cars.'
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.58,0:36:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If we have to identify the best\Nbudget supercar, it's the Audi,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.46,0:36:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no question about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.86,0:36:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have to identify the best\Ncar, it's the Ferrari. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.54,0:37:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't. Yes, it is. Well, it\Nisn't. The McLaren is a better car.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.38,0:37:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a better supercar. You\Ndidn't say supercar. You said car.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.58,0:37:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, best supercar.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.26,0:37:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now you see that\Nthe best supercar is the Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.30,0:37:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The best car is the McLaren.\NYeah, but if I'm buying a supercar,\NI'm buying...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.78,0:37:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,..and the winner of this test,\Nso far... is the Audi.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.50,0:37:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,..is the Audi.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.58,0:37:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd go with that entirely. Yes.\NNot very useful for the viewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.98,0:37:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,'With dinner served, we carried\Non trying to reach a verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.78,0:37:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,'But it was hopeless.'
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.10,0:37:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is, but the Ferrari, they've\Ninjected some magic into...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.90,0:37:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,With the roof off, it is properly\Ngood. No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.94,0:37:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,£70,000 will buy a cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.46,0:37:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it interfere with this debate\Nif I was suddenly and violently sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.98,0:37:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's waiting for a photo\Nto download on his computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.74,0:37:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He's sitting there going,\N"Buffering. Buffering."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.58,0:38:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, look, we want to make it\Nabsolutely clear,\Nthat airport is not a film set.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.94,0:38:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It opened five years ago,\Nthen it went bust,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.90,0:38:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,then it closed down last year. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.22,0:38:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing, though,\Nif you think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.34,0:38:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have unused things\Nlying around -\NI've got a bread maker and a wok -
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.30,0:38:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't got an international\Nairport. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.78,0:38:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,About that, did you see what\Nthat runway did to my Ferrari?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.06,0:38:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm, and you should see\Nwhat happens to it later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.62,0:38:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we, Richard Hammond?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.22,0:38:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think you really want to\Nhang on and watch that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.86,0:38:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe turn over to Countryfile, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.70,0:38:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,James... James, would you stay with\NTop Gear, or switch over to see\NAdam's farm. Let me have a think.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.26,0:38:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'd stay with Top Gear.\NI'd stay with Top Gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.86,0:38:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, that's then, this is now,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.22,0:38:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and we must put a star\Nin our Reasonably Priced Car.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.74,0:38:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, my guest, my guest tonight\Nis best known for dying
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.82,0:38:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and then coming back to life.\NBut it is not the baby Jesus.\NLAUGHTER
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.58,0:38:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the man who played\NSherlock Holmes on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.14,0:38:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen,\Nplease welcome Benedict Cumberbatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.14,0:39:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.\NWow. Wow, wow, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.14,0:39:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.14,0:39:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that was a welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.18,0:39:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a welcome from a lot\Nof people who want to know
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.82,0:39:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,how you're not dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.74,0:39:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when I jump off, there's\Na helicopter with Mycroft
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.22,0:39:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in it dressed as a woman\Nand an inflatable skirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.90,0:39:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he takes a pill,\Nwhich basically\Nmeans that the helicopter...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.18,0:39:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to tell anyone.\NI can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.10,0:39:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, I was really enjoying that!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.30,0:39:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Cos it was obviously\None of the most written-about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.18,0:39:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and talked-about events in modern\Ntelevision history.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.54,0:39:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.30,0:39:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I sort of missed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.54,0:39:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The furore at home, anyway.\NI was abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.98,0:39:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that it went on for weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.82,0:39:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It did, you actually fell off a\Nbuilding and then you're not dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.38,0:39:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.50,0:39:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we saw you dead, but anyway...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.82,0:40:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When do you find out how that\Nhad been achieved?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.38,0:40:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it'll be some time near\Nthe end of this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.54,0:40:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or at the beginning of next.\NThat's what we're aiming for.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.10,0:40:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, more recently, we've seen\Nyou in the new Star Trek movie.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.66,0:40:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone seen that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.98,0:40:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.02,0:40:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you are a damn good baddie, if I\Nmay be so bold. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.74,0:40:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It does beg the question, why are\Nthe Americans incapable of casting
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.30,0:40:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,an American as the baddie in any\Nfilm? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.10,0:40:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a sort of pet theory that they\Ndo vowels, which are sort of warm
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.86,0:40:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and loving and feeling, and we do\Nconsonants,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.98,0:40:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which are sharp and\Nintelligent and thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.22,0:40:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's as hippy, mad,\Nleftfield as I can get with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.70,0:40:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We sound more intelligent?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.26,0:40:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of, and maybe that's\Nscary for them, I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.82,0:40:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,End of my US career!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.26,0:40:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was going to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.46,0:40:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things I must ask is, now\Nthat you've appeared in Star Trek,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.50,0:40:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,do you find yourself being\Napproached
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.22,0:40:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by those of a Trekkie disposition?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.74,0:40:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The ones I have\Nmet are remarkably normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.62,0:40:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a bit like, "I-I'm quite\Na Trekkie fan, actually." You are?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.94,0:41:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that was me pretending\Nto be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.34,0:41:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, OK! You're such a good actor,\NI thought actually you were one!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.90,0:41:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fooled you there, Jeremy!\NFooled you there!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.26,0:41:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't, actually,\NI wasn't a Trekkie.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.50,0:41:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched the first film, I was very\Ninto that, and then I obviously did
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.54,0:41:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit of research as far as\Nwhat I was about to do in the canon,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.62,0:41:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I really got into it.\NIt was great to be a part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.62,0:41:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You do worry about saying that you\Nlike Star Trek,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.82,0:41:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but I've always liked it, ever since\Nit was Kirk and Spock,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.38,0:41:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,right the way through,\NJean-Luc Picard.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.38,0:41:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's a great relationship.\NA great relationship. Yeah... No?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.18,0:41:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see that -\Nwhat relationship?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.86,0:41:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Between Kirk, Spock and Bones.\NI think those three...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.58,0:41:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it, if I talk about\Na relationship between two men
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.06,0:41:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in a drama, they're immediately\Nat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.06,0:41:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The worldwide inter-lie will just\Ngo, splat,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.66,0:41:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a load of fan fiction which\Nhas me and John Watson
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.46,0:41:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,floating in space in a bed,\Nhandcuffed to one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.86,0:41:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just with handcuffs either!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.74,0:41:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I could write that tonight,\Nit would be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.54,0:41:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're from an acting family. I am,\Nmy mum and dad are both actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.26,0:42:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum... Both, actually... My car\Nhistory sort of begins with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.46,0:42:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I sort of was introduced to\Ncars by them...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.42,0:42:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's interesting, we've got\Na photograph of your mum here, look.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.26,0:42:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, my mum didn't have\Na car like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.18,0:42:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite cool. It's very cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.50,0:42:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that from a Gerry Anderson?\NIt is, it's from UFO.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.22,0:42:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. No, she was in UFO?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.74,0:42:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She was in UFO. So that obviously\Nwasn't her car, that is a...?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.06,0:42:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but she did drive it, and it was\Ndriveable. She had an MGT...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.54,0:42:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,An MGB, I should say, a hatchback.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.34,0:42:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a hatchback,\Nsorry - a soft top. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.38,0:42:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But all cars before I was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.78,0:42:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was born,\Nit all got a bit sensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.70,0:42:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She had a Mini, which was great.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.94,0:42:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Cos that was my first car.\NWas it? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.46,0:42:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Your first car was actually\Na proper Mini, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.50,0:42:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A little Mini. Crash it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.90,0:42:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but I did reverse after\Na night out
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.50,0:42:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,over a very large rock on a driveway
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.94,0:42:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gearstick just went,\N"Thunk," right through the chassis\Nof the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.94,0:42:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, next car was a...?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.54,0:42:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A Golf Mitsubishi Colt from 1982,\Nhatchback. A Golf?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.94,0:42:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. No, not a Golf, sorry.\NMitsubishi Colt.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.34,0:42:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your MGT\Nand a Golf Mitsubishi! Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.18,0:43:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting my... I'm cross-splicing\Nin some future world of cars!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.74,0:43:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of car\Njumbling going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.70,0:43:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good job I don't do\Nyour job - I'd be rubbish at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.34,0:43:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good job I don't do yours -
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.18,0:43:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I've no idea how to fly a spaceship\Nor punch anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.14,0:43:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Or act. That can be taught. I got\Ntaught that. What, how to punch?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.42,0:43:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Hollywood fu, it was great\Nfun.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.90,0:43:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you punch like... Do you punch\Nwith that side of your hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.86,0:43:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? When you punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.50,0:43:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you're trying to wipe\Na windscreen or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.42,0:43:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No, when you punch somebody,\Ncos I've often... You sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.22,0:43:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, you're quite tight and\Nit's all from the waist,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.94,0:43:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but you have to sell it a bit more\Nfor the camera, so you arc it round\Na bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.34,0:43:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You could try it. Shall we try it\Nnow? Shall we try a fake punch?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.94,0:43:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.50,0:43:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it turns into a real one?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.42,0:43:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give and you receive.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.42,0:43:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I like being the dominant one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.02,0:43:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's the camera. That one?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.94,0:43:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Facing me. You're actually directing\Nnow! Yeah! Facing you...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.06,0:43:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I ready for this punch? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.82,0:44:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When I get to about there, you can\Nmove your head. But what if I don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.90,0:44:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.30,0:44:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Is anybody... Your dry-cleaning\Nbills when my nose...!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.54,0:44:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Are you ready? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.06,0:44:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.70,0:44:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did that look all right?\NHe knows, they know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.94,0:44:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had many actors on the show\Nover the years, sitting there,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.86,0:44:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but we've never had one who's been\Ncarjacked before.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.38,0:44:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.58,0:44:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It is, but you were genuinely\Ncarjacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.94,0:44:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was genuinely carjacked. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.94,0:44:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Scary? How did it happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.46,0:44:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.86,0:44:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to emphasise,\Nnot just because I love South Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.98,0:44:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and South Africans,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.18,0:44:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was a small event in a very\Nbig country, and we were very lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.82,0:44:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We were on a bumpy dirt track\Nand had gone onto the N2,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.78,0:44:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the major trunk\Nroad down the east coast,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.62,0:44:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the front right tyre blew\Nand these guys surrounded us,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.54,0:44:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff went on with belongings\Nand we were pushed about a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.30,0:44:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I was put in the boot of the car,\Nthough, at one point,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.66,0:45:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.46,0:45:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, "Maybe I could diffuse\Nthe brake lights,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.46,0:45:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"then the police..."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.54,0:45:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no policeman in South Africa\Nis going to pull over a car
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.74,0:45:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,full of men at midnight to\Nquestion a broken taillight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.98,0:45:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was very scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.62,0:45:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When they got you out again, did\Nthey not put a duvet over your head?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.18,0:45:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At one point,\Nstuff was being thrown out the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.74,0:45:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We were underneath this underpass
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.90,0:45:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and these juggernauts were just\Ncharging over
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.78,0:45:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sound cover\Nwould be perfect for a quiet pop.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.22,0:45:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this duvet got thrown out, just\Nwent over our head, and I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.58,0:45:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"Again, it's the pillow thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.26,0:45:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"it's going to be a muffler for\Na gunshot."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.74,0:45:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I kind of came to terms\Nwith mortality
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.94,0:45:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and dying on my own about four\Ntimes in the space of half an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.46,0:45:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing\Nwent on for about two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.46,0:45:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We mustn't put people off southern\NAfrica. No, we mustn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.14,0:45:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big, beautiful place. It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.70,0:45:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could just ignore all that, it\Ndoesn't really happen! Cut that!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.90,0:45:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so, you came down here to\Ndo your lap. Oh, BLEEP!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.94,0:45:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And how was it out there?\NIt was really good fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.06,0:46:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The first couple of laps, I couldn't\Nsee the wood for the trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.94,0:46:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but as it went on, I think I got...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.54,0:46:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I bettered my times later on,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.86,0:46:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,so I was obviously learning\Nsomething. How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.34,0:46:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,People would go, "Mmm."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.02,0:46:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, just from people's "Mmm"?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.02,0:46:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told you did more laps than\Nany guest we've had.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.18,0:46:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's so shaming!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.22,0:46:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd like to see the fastest lap?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.74,0:46:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.78,0:46:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.66,0:46:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.90,0:46:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.06,0:46:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We are away.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.50,0:46:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yippee ki-yay, mother-BLEEP!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.86,0:46:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A fan of The Hangover is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.54,0:46:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at it grip,\Nwith a lifetime warranty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.62,0:46:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not bad.\NIs that all right? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.86,0:46:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It is hot in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.94,0:46:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's no excuse, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.54,0:46:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you have the air conditioning\Noff or on? Off. Good man.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.14,0:46:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A bit wide through there,\Nmaybe costing you half a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.34,0:46:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Gear change, gear change, gear\Nchange, gear change. So... boom.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.42,0:47:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, like the Sundance Kid there,\Nvery quick mover! Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.70,0:47:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Bit slow, but at least you're not\Nskidding about.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.82,0:47:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't really used all\Nthe track - or, indeed, any of it.\NAnyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.18,0:47:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Use the track, Benedict.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.14,0:47:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, Alec Guinness\Nin the Reasonably Priced Car!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.74,0:47:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Moved those, that was well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.50,0:47:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And now here it is,\Nsecond-to-last corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.98,0:47:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy crap, this is scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.54,0:47:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that is\Npretty much perfect. Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.38,0:47:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That really is perfect, Gambon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.74,0:47:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, fast. Ooh, fast,\Nbut not Jimmy Carr. Across the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.18,0:47:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, not bad! That is all right.\NThat is all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.26,0:47:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the times we have so far\Nin our Reasonably Priced Car.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.82,0:47:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, crikey.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.78,0:47:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do we think?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.42,0:47:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.98,0:47:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe faster than Warwick, I'd be\Nhappy with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.46,0:47:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster than Warwick, at 1:46.8.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.14,0:48:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you're aiming.\NThat's very high, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.22,0:48:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Benedict Cumberbatch,\Nyou... are leaning forwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.06,0:48:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't make my time faster,\Nwill it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.82,0:48:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't got much space\Nleft on here!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.70,0:48:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then shorten the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.78,0:48:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it in one...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.02,0:48:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,..40...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.26,0:48:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,..7.8.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.14,0:48:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! So you're not faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.46,0:48:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I can live with that.\NIt's in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.90,0:48:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What I've got here is a list of all\Nthe other people who've
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.62,0:48:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared on Star Trek.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.54,0:48:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If it makes you feel any better,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.98,0:48:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jean-Luc Picard, 1:50 dead.\NOh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.10,0:48:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're faster than he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.26,0:48:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But the previous baddie in the last\Nfilm, Eric Bana, 1:47.5,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.42,0:48:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was in the wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.10,0:48:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Phwoar. So Eric Bana is faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.62,0:49:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't really find any\Ncomfort at all for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.66,0:49:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I've just got to come back,\Nyou've got to invite me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.22,0:49:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I basically brought you down here\Nand ruined your day.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.70,0:49:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah! I do apologise for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.38,0:49:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has been an enormous\Npleasure. Likewise, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.34,0:49:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Best of luck with the new Sherlock,\Nabsolute joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.66,0:49:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen,\NBenedict Cumberbatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.74,0:49:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, tonight, we are heading for\NMadrid
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.98,0:49:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,in three convertible supercars.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.94,0:49:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, we've found Spain to be\Nfull of brand-new things that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.82,0:49:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody seems to be using.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.50,0:49:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely. We spent\Nthe night in an unwanted house,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.78,0:49:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,where Jeremy had cooked us dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.14,0:49:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we rejoin the action\Nthe following morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.98,0:49:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,'After a hectic night on the\Nlavatory, we headed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.34,0:49:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,'But after just 100 yards...'
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.98,0:50:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I've ruined my Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.34,0:50:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,'..I hit a bollard.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.54,0:50:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,'Luckily, though, my colleagues\Ndidn't make a big deal of it.'
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.62,0:50:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond, look out for that signpost\Ndead ahead of you. Hammond, careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.62,0:50:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Block of flats on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.78,0:50:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Please kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.78,0:50:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Breaking a Ferrari is\Nan especially bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.06,0:50:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like kicking a rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.98,0:50:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond, when we get on\Nthe motorway,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.78,0:50:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be driving quite fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.02,0:50:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it might be 70 miles an hour, you'll\Nreally need to concentrate there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.54,0:50:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hammond, move right, mind the Armco.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.34,0:50:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They're never going to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.78,0:50:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,'Sure enough,\Nthe abuse kept on coming.'
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.34,0:50:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Two big metal pillars, Hammond.\NDon't... Do you see them? Mind that!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.98,0:50:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That way! You're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.18,0:51:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,'Happily, after several uneventful\Nmiles on yet another empty motorway,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.14,0:51:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,'we were finally approaching Madrid.'
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.98,0:51:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I know capital cities often escape\Nthe worst of austerity times
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.42,0:51:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,like these, so hopefully that'll\Nstill be a busy old place.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.98,0:51:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,'However...'
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.62,0:51:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.86,0:51:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.02,0:51:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There are thousands of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.26,0:51:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This crash was clearly bigger\Nthan ever I realised.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.06,0:51:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, look on the upside - there's\Nno-one for Hammond to run over.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.26,0:52:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,'And that thought gave me\Nyet another brilliant idea.'
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.18,0:52:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody is driving on that road.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.86,0:52:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are you suggesting?\NOr that road.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.22,0:52:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm saying is, we turn this\Ntown into a street circuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.06,0:52:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ship The Stig out, he sets a time in\Na car of some sort
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.34,0:52:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and we try and match it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.30,0:52:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an ambitious plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.98,0:52:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How hard can it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.58,0:52:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A few tyres, bits of barrier.\NThat's an excellent grandstand.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.70,0:52:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All the residents - if there were\Nany - could sit on those balconies\Nand watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.22,0:52:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Bernie Ecclestone will now be\Nleaning forward in his chair and\Ngoing,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.46,0:52:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Good idea."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.22,0:52:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Madrid Grand Prix,\Ncoming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.30,0:52:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,'Having sorted out a course,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.42,0:52:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'James and I set about making\Nit into an actual track.'
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.38,0:52:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do them regular\Nif you're going that fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.34,0:52:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's uphill. Yeah.\NKeep going! Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.30,0:53:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ferrari rosso.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.70,0:53:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you crash into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.06,0:53:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this will effectively repair\Nthe damage you've done to your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.86,0:53:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,'Because of my problem with\Nmanual labour,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.02,0:53:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,'I went off to collect The Stig.'
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.34,0:53:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is the start, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.98,0:53:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful. So this one goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.94,0:53:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,James, just do them when I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.94,0:53:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,..getting the...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.70,0:53:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No! That's... What the bloody hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.06,0:53:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.90,0:53:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.58,0:53:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The Stig's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.54,0:53:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.18,0:53:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'With the circuit complete and\Nchristened, we unwrapped The Stig
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.58,0:53:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,'so he could set a benchmark time in\Na supercharged Jaguar convertible.'
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.82,0:54:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, are you ready with\Nthe stopwatch, James May? Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.10,0:54:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Bradley Cooper will start it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.66,0:54:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Three, two, one!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.54,0:54:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a dirty, dirty sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.90,0:54:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look at that!\NHe's got his tail out,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.14,0:54:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,going round the Rockery of\NGibraltar.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.70,0:54:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'Because this was a street circuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.58,0:54:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,'it was lined with wheel-killing\Nkerbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.06,0:54:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,'And there was even a speed hump.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.54,0:54:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,'But these things were of no\Nmoment to The Stig.'
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.10,0:54:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! 57 and a half seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.26,0:54:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.70,0:55:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,'We then set off on a sighting lap,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.38,0:55:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,'knowing that\Nif we wanted to beat The Stig,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.50,0:55:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,'we'd have to average at least\N60 miles an hour.'
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.14,0:55:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That is alarming there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.70,0:55:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,'Even though our cars were faster\Nthan the Jag,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.26,0:55:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,'it looked like a tall order.'
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.90,0:55:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, here we go, this is it,\Nyou and me, little Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.90,0:55:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's our chance,\Ngive it everything you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.30,0:55:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Three, two, one!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.58,0:55:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Really fast start.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.58,0:55:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,On the limiter,\Nround the Rockery of Gibraltar.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.50,0:55:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn it. This thing will grip,\NRichard.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.02,0:56:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Left that late. Back on the power\Nas soon as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.82,0:56:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That was quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.74,0:56:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the chicane. This is monstrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.58,0:56:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, thread it through.\NThat is tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.58,0:56:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the final straight,\Nup towards the finish line.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.74,0:56:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all I've got,\Neverything I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.90,0:56:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Little Fezza, I really hope I've made\Nup for crashing you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.14,0:56:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,'With my work done,\Nit was Mr Slowly's turn.'
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.30,0:56:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Three, two, one!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.50,0:57:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, it sounds second!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.78,0:57:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Third!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.66,0:57:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,James May, ladies\Nand gentlemen, hit third!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.62,0:57:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a left-hander somewhere.\NThere it is. Throw him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.82,0:57:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Howard of Effingham.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.70,0:57:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, tricky gear change with\Nthe gear... Oh, BLEEP!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.14,0:57:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No-one expects the Spanish\Nspeed hump.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.02,0:57:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice and straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.86,0:57:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly bloody killed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.30,0:57:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,'Finally,\Nit was the turn of the McLaren.'
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.06,0:58:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Active, aero, sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.34,0:58:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.34,0:58:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Three, two, one!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.50,0:58:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, that was launch control!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.42,0:58:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Concentrate, Jeremy, concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.18,0:58:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.06,0:58:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Massive tail slide there!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.10,0:58:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And on to the Golden Hind straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.38,0:58:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,91 miles an hour there.\NDown to second.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.34,0:59:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, power!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.34,0:59:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.42,0:59:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to say, our street circuit\Nwas a million times better
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.94,0:59:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,than Spain's other one in Valencia.\NIt's one of the most boring street\Ncircuits in the world. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.10,0:59:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The only problem I had was,\Nyou know the Lord Howard of\NEffingham chicane? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.38,0:59:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You really wanted first,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.78,0:59:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but I couldn't ever get it in the\NMcLaren. Trying to jam it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.42,0:59:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem I had is when you get to\Nthe "no-one expects\Nthe Spanish speed hump". Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.30,0:59:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to go wide and try to hit it\Nreasonably square, cos if you got it\Nat an angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.66,0:59:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd be banged into the kerb.\NAnd then, you'd smash your wheel\Noff! Yeah, absolutely. Yes, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.86,0:59:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I have the results here.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.54,0:59:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the... well, there's no other way\Nto put this...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.42,0:59:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,..the fastest car around\Nour magnificent track was...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.90,0:59:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ferrari! Yeah, it was! It wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.34,1:00:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it was, cos if you look,\Nthere's the numbers
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.82,1:00:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,next to the names, the one next to\Nmine is the smallest, that means...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.74,1:00:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, Hammond. The Ferrari was\Nthe fastest in the first lap.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.94,1:00:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was a one-lap event.\NIt wasn't a one-lap event!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.66,1:00:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, cos then, we parcel\Nthe cameras away, OK,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.42,1:00:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we kept going,\Nas you remember, and by the end,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.58,1:00:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the McLaren was not just faster\Nthan the Ferrari,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.82,1:00:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but faster than The Stig.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.02,1:00:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But that wasn't the end, because then\NThe Stig went out again in the Jag
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.26,1:00:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and was faster than the McLaren. Yes.\NHang on, that wasn't the end either,\Nbecause, if you remember,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.62,1:00:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it then started raining and in the\Nrain, the Audi was the fastest
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.74,1:00:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its four-wheel drive.\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.30,1:00:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't very good, is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.42,1:00:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not very clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.02,1:00:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, what we're saying is,\Nat various different points,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.78,1:00:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,all of them were the fastest. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.94,1:00:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I've got the results\Nof everything over here,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.22,1:00:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,all the categories.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.62,1:00:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And speed, yes, we decided\Nthat was a dead heat for all three.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.26,1:00:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no, I mean, on the night,\Nit was the Ferrari.\NIt wasn't the Ferrari...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.74,1:00:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a one-lap event... It was\Nthe McLa... Would you two shut up?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.74,1:01:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Quietness, that was also a dead heat\Nbetween the Audi and the McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.02,1:01:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Discretion, the Audi.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.14,1:01:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Economy, that was the Audi.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.50,1:01:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Value was the Audi, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.06,1:01:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,finally, equipment...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.30,1:01:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that was the Audi.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.10,1:01:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A bit clearer, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.66,1:01:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fairly comprehensive win there\Nfor the Audi. Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.18,1:01:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, James May, of the three cars,\Nknowing what we know now,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.82,1:01:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which would you choose to buy?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.10,1:01:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.10,1:01:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's the Ferrari. And you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.94,1:01:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... McLaren. Interesting. Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.82,1:01:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'd have the Ferrari. Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.10,1:01:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the McLaren is absolutely\Nbrilliant,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.82,1:01:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but the Ferrari is just\Na little bit more special.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.78,1:01:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we're finally saying\Nis we'd all three have a car
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.82,1:01:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that dissolves if you drive it\Ntoo quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.14,1:01:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.74,1:01:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But on that bombshell, we can end.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.82,1:01:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for watching.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.70,1:02:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,See you all again next week.\NTake care, good night!
